13:56.387 --> 14:01.874
Again the amplified version which I'll read in a moment helps us with this but again

14:02.370 --> 14:11.239
As I've argued with the other verse in Hebrews 10, this is not the point of the verse for two reasons to begin with.

14:12.400 --> 14:20.788
First, there are lots of scriptures that talk about people falling away and coming back again, the prodigal son.

14:23.210 --> 14:29.196
The prodigal son was somebody who went away from the father's house, repented and came back.

14:29.716 --> 14:31.538
That's one possible.

14:31.746 --> 14:33.068
solution to this.

14:35.051 --> 14:37.134
The other thing is this.

14:39.617 --> 14:50.112
It says here in the way that they structured the verse, it is not to say that the person who falls away to come back would be re-crucifying the Son of God again.

14:50.152 --> 14:56.261
It's saying by going away they're re-crucifying him again.

14:57.162 --> 14:58.264
Why is that important?

14:58.284 --> 14:59.666
Here's the amplified version.

15:01.058 --> 15:07.246
The Amplified Version of the Bible says this, and then when they're fallen away, it's impossible to bring them back to repentance.

15:07.666 --> 15:11.191
Since again, they nail the Son of God to the cross.

15:11.872 --> 15:22.565
So as far as they're concerned, they are treating the death of Christ as if they are not saved by it and holding him up to a public disgrace.

15:24.628 --> 15:29.714
Another way you could paraphrase that is basically by walking away

15:30.018 --> 15:37.388
and putting Jesus back on as to some guy who died on a cross, you're saying, I don't want anything to do with this guy.

15:37.609 --> 15:48.083
Once you have taken that position, you are making it impossible for you to come back to him because you're living under the lie that Jesus didn't die and rise again for your sins.

15:48.544 --> 15:50.747
So it's not having any benefit for you.

15:51.428 --> 15:58.738
It's not that you couldn't come back and God wouldn't welcome you when you came back, but you've got the kind of mindset now

15:59.138 --> 16:00.580
written Jesus off.

16:01.420 --> 16:02.802
So what are you going to do now?

16:02.902 --> 16:06.886
It's impossible for you to come back because you've come to a position that he's no good to you.

16:08.348 --> 16:19.039
It's not saying that God wouldn't welcome you back or it's impossible for him to bring you back, but you're putting yourself in an impossible situation when you write Jesus off as your savior.

16:23.623 --> 16:26.066
I could say more on this, but I would have to go

16:26.210 --> 16:32.561
labor the verses than the context in the original language more, and that's not the point of this message.

16:34.104 --> 16:42.740
The point of this message is that the reverses which might scare you, but they don't mean what maybe you've been told that they mean.

16:42.780 --> 16:50.674
Now I'm not saying that there aren't verses in the Bible, there shouldn't get us a bit of a squeaky bum time.

16:51.650 --> 17:00.983
And I'm not saying you can treat God, however you like, do whatever you want, think, speak, act as if nothing matters and just go, okay, it's okay, Jesus paid it all.

17:02.906 --> 17:03.947
When I die, I'm going to go to heaven.

17:04.067 --> 17:05.109
This is all about him, not about me.

17:06.551 --> 17:08.553
That is also not what I'm arguing.

17:09.675 --> 17:20.690
What I am saying to you that if somebody is genuinely born again and saved, someone genuinely recognizes that Jesus is the way, the truth and the life, they've had the spirit of God come and live within them.

17:22.626 --> 17:30.497
If they do walk away, it's because they're choosing to reject Him, not because they've done so many naughty things that God is rejecting them.

17:30.537 --> 17:37.367
And there's a difference to why people move away from God.

17:37.387 --> 17:43.796
One is the choice of will and the other is to say, well, maybe God's kicking you out.

17:44.137 --> 17:47.922
Now, God disciplines people, God corrects people.

17:49.090 --> 17:56.261
And maybe if someone can continue to deliberately keep on sinning, you can question whether they ever really believed in God in the first place.

17:58.424 --> 18:02.270
Pigs wallow in the mud, sheep go in the mud, but they get out.

18:03.712 --> 18:08.539
Sometimes our habits and our actions reveal our true nature.

18:11.063 --> 18:13.026
So I'm not arguing you can do whatever you want.

18:13.126 --> 18:14.248
You can behave however you want.

18:14.308 --> 18:18.514
I think God doesn't care about that because he just looks at Jesus and ignores your behavior.

18:18.850 --> 18:30.268
What I am saying is the reverse is which would initially seem to say, well, just be careful, you might just do too much and God rejects you, but that's not what those verses are actually saying.

18:32.631 --> 18:38.520
There are other verses to kind of assure us that Jesus has forgiveness for us if we repent.

18:38.620 --> 18:43.708
The Lord's prayer, forgive us today our sins as we forgive those who sin against us.

18:44.269 --> 18:47.474
The assumption is that there's something for you to confess every day.

18:48.514 --> 18:50.737
in terms of your forgiveness.

18:50.898 --> 18:58.689
Proverbs 28, 13, whoever conceals their sins does not prosper, but the one who confesses and renounces them finds mercy.

19:01.673 --> 19:11.688
Matthew 18, 21 to 22, it says, then Peter came to the Lord Jesus and asked, Lord, how many times shall I forgive my brother or sister who sins against me?

19:12.069 --> 19:13.511
Up to seven times.

19:13.871 --> 19:15.634
And Jesus answered, I'll tell you not,

19:15.746 --> 19:18.550
seven times, but 77 times.

19:18.810 --> 19:21.915
Do you think God holds himself to a lower standard than he holds you to?

19:21.935 --> 19:25.660
I don't think so.

19:27.402 --> 19:29.725
I think there is grace for you.

19:29.745 --> 19:32.749
There are times when we need to repent.

19:33.190 --> 19:34.912
There are times when we need to acknowledge sin.

19:35.213 --> 19:38.698
There are times that we need to say to God, I have failed and I've fallen short.

19:38.978 --> 19:44.786
We cannot treat God's grace and his kindness and mercy as if it means nothing, if it's cheap,

19:46.306 --> 19:56.461
We shouldn't ever, if we follow Jesus, deliberately keep on sinning because we just presume that God's not looking at our behavior but the works of Jesus.

19:57.563 --> 19:59.265
Because that is disrespect.

19:59.966 --> 20:04.353
That is a lack of care and concern for the great gift that God has given us.

20:06.516 --> 20:16.210
But you've got to wonder if people ever were to do that on the long term, over the long term, that maybe they didn't have a real relationship

20:16.290 --> 20:17.451
in the first place.

20:18.312 --> 20:23.377
The reason the prodigal son came home was because he knew who he was going home to.

20:23.417 --> 20:36.250
The prodigal son left his sin and came home because he already knew his father's identity and what it was like to live in his father's house.

20:41.795 --> 20:44.818
So I believe the Bible supports this notion

20:48.034 --> 20:53.121
that we are saved by grace through faith.

20:53.662 --> 20:56.586
It's not by works, no one can boast.

20:57.768 --> 21:08.023
You cannot do anything to achieve the forgiveness and the mercy of God except repent and believe and confess.

21:10.847 --> 21:12.690
But if someone has done that,

21:13.826 --> 21:27.143
You would expect a life that while it fails many, many times, it comes back to a place where it asks God for mercy to continue to flow.

21:27.203 --> 21:41.842
If someone continues to sin and do what is wrong and never comes back to God under conviction and says, God, I'm sorry, then you have to question their conversion in the first place.

21:44.194 --> 21:48.460
because prodigals come home to a father that they know.

21:50.963 --> 21:55.769
Pigs swallow in the mud, but sheep, after they've been in the mud, they get out.

21:56.770 --> 22:08.405
There is something about sin and whether someone actually ultimately repents for that sin that reveals the nature of the reality of what relationship they had and who they are.

22:10.027 --> 22:12.050
There are verses in the Bible.

22:12.962 --> 22:23.158
where there are warnings against this false prophet, this false teacher, this person and that person, people who once walked with the church, once confessed Christ and they seem to drift away.

22:23.198 --> 22:39.302
But the Bible, while warning us against the possibility of the dangers of falling away, doesn't base our salvation on our performance.

22:39.322 --> 22:41.906
So there's two things for you to take from this today.

22:43.362 --> 23:04.915
The first is the reassurance that if you fear that there are times when you let God down and you're concerned that you have just done too much for God to continue saving you, I want to reassure you that God's mercies are new every morning.

23:06.537 --> 23:09.522
Great is his faithfulness.

23:11.010 --> 23:20.365
And 1 John 1 8 9, if we confess our sins, God is faithful and just to forgive us our sins and to cleanse us from all unrighteousness.

23:22.708 --> 23:30.460
But don't treat God's grace as a license to sin because it's not.

23:31.682 --> 23:36.690
And if that's your attitude, then have a look at your own heart

23:36.994 --> 23:43.981
and ask yourself the question whether you've really fully understood who has saved you and what he saved you from.

23:44.021 --> 23:51.628
But if you have known the Father and loved the Father, you've trusted in him as Lord and Savior.

23:52.029 --> 23:59.876
And even if you make a number of mistakes, God's grace is sufficient for you.

23:59.916 --> 24:05.682
God's grace is sufficient.

24:05.826 --> 24:06.226
for you.

24:06.427 --> 24:14.254
I'm going to finish with reading this verse from Romans chapter 8, all these verses from Romans chapter 8.

24:24.844 --> 24:29.489
Paul says this to the church in Romans verse 31 of Romans chapter 8, I'll read to the end of the chapter.

24:30.069 --> 24:31.911
