24:31.971 --> 24:35.154
If God is for us, who can be against us?

24:35.522 --> 24:43.173
He who did not spare his own son, but gave him up for us all, how will he not also, along with him, graciously give us all things?

24:44.154 --> 24:47.479
Who will bring any charge against those whom God has chosen?

24:48.019 --> 24:53.187
It is God who justifies not your works, not your performance.

24:54.088 --> 24:55.730
Who is he that condemns

24:56.002 --> 25:02.408
Christ Jesus who died more than that, he was raised to life and he's at the right hand side of God also interceding for us.

25:02.869 --> 25:05.511
Who shall separate us from the love of Christ?

25:05.972 --> 25:16.102
Shall trouble or hardship or persecution or famine or nakedness or danger or sword as it is written for your sake, we face death all day long.

25:16.922 --> 25:18.764
We are considered as sheet to be slaughtered.

25:18.824 --> 25:22.508
Knowing all these things, we are more than conquerors through him who loved us.

25:22.828 --> 25:24.690
For I am convinced that neither death

25:25.058 --> 25:44.125
nor life nor angels nor demons nor the present nor the future nor any powers neither height nor depth nor anything else in all creation will be able to separate us from the love of God that is in Christ Jesus our Lord.

25:46.969 --> 25:52.978
Some try to argue that's maybe not salvation that Paul is addressing there possibly.

25:53.570 --> 26:02.063
but it does talk about the security of God's love and the fact that we are held ultimately by Him, not by our good works.

26:03.866 --> 26:11.678
It is God who forgives, it is God who justifies, it is the work of Christ, and it is to His glory that we are saved.

26:12.659 --> 26:17.266
We don't, as genuine followers of Jesus, believe in cheap grace.

26:18.370 --> 26:24.820
But neither do we live every day nervous that if we make one too many mistakes, God is going to cut us out of his family.

26:25.041 --> 26:29.288
Because that's not how a loving father works.

26:30.169 --> 26:30.690
Let's pray.

26:32.252 --> 26:38.322
Yeah, fathers, we've wrestled with your word this morning as to what we think it means or it doesn't mean, Lord, or we just pray.

26:39.746 --> 26:44.030
that as we maybe reflect on these verses after today, we wrestle with them.

26:44.050 --> 26:55.821
And what they mean and don't mean, Lord God, I just pray that your word of your spirit will come through where people that believe in truth and sometimes scripture isn't immediately obvious as to what it means.

26:57.263 --> 27:09.074
But Lord God, through the understanding of your spirit and through hard work and careful study, Lord God, we can find there is truth that where there was once fear, there are things to be assured about.

27:09.570 --> 27:11.273
and comforted by.

27:11.293 --> 27:24.252
And, Lord God, we just stand on your word today that if we confess with our mouth and believe with our hearts that Jesus is Lord, we shall be saved.

27:24.973 --> 27:29.881
You are a good Father, a loving God, and we trust you with our eternity.

27:30.442 --> 27:34.708
In Jesus' name, amen.

27:34.728 --> 27:36.250
We've come to the end of this week's message.

27:36.851 --> 27:38.674
We hope you've been impacted and inspired.

27:39.266 --> 27:46.130
Please keep up-to-date with everything that's happening by visiting our website at www.livechurchgoingsin.com.

